  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What should I do if I lost my Chase debit card?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear you've lost your Chase debit card. Here's a step-by-step guide to help you address the situation promptly and securely:\n\n1. **Report the Loss Immediately:**\n   - **Call Chase Customer Service:**\n     - **Phone Number:** For U.S. customers, you can reach Chase's customer service at **1-800-935-9935**. This number is available 24/7 for lost or stolen cards.\n     - **Via Mobile App:** If you have the Chase Mobile app, you can report your card lost or stolen directly through the app.\n     - **Online Banking:** Log in to your [Chase Online](https://www.chase.com/) account and navigate to the \"Customer Service\" or \"Account Services\" section to report your card as lost.\n\n2. **Lock Your Card Temporarily (If Available):**\n   - Chase offers a feature to **lock your card** via the mobile app or online banking. This prevents unauthorized transactions while you search for your card or wait for a replacement.\n\n3. **Review Recent Account Activity:**\n   - **Check Transactions:** After reporting the loss, review your recent account activity for any unauthorized or suspicious transactions.\n   - **Dispute Unauthorized Charges:** If you notice any unfamiliar transactions, contact Chase immediately to dispute them.\n\n4. **Request a Replacement Card:**\n   - **Automatic Replacement:** When you report a lost card, Chase typically issues a replacement automatically.\n   - **Confirm Details:** Ensure that your mailing address is up-to-date to receive the new card promptly.\n   - **Choose Card Features:** If applicable, select any preferences for your new card, such as design or additional security features.\n\n5. **Update Automatic Payments:**\n   - **Recurring Payments:** After receiving your new debit card, update your card information for any automatic payments or subscriptions linked to your lost card to avoid disruptions.\n\n6. **Set Up Account Alerts:**\n   - **Notifications:** Enable account alerts via email or SMS through Chase's online banking or mobile app to stay informed about any future account activity.\n\n7. **Secure Your Account:**\n   - **Change Online Banking Password:** As a precaution, consider updating your online banking password and enabling two-factor authentication for added security.\n   - **Monitor Regularly:** Continue to monitor your account regularly for any unusual activity.\n\n8. **Dispose of Old Information Securely:**\n   - **Shred Documents:** If you had any documents with your debit card information, ensure they are shredded or disposed of securely to prevent identity theft.\n\n**Contact Information:**\n- **Chase Customer Service:** 1-800-935-9935 (available 24/7)\n- **Chase Online Support:** [Chase Contact Page](https://www.chase.com/digital/resources/contact-us)\n\n**Additional Tips:**\n- **Keep Emergency Numbers Handy:** Save Chase's customer service number in your phone for quick access in the future.\n- **Stay Vigilant:** Regularly monitor your accounts, even after resolving the immediate issue, to ensure no unauthorized activities occur.\n\nBy taking these steps promptly, you can minimize potential risks associated with a lost debit card and ensure your finances remain secure.",
